eturn True\n```\n\nThis solution checks if the array `nums` was originally sorted in non-decreasing order and then rotated some number of positions. The key observation is that in a rotated sorted array, there should be at most one place where the order is violated (i.e., where a number is greater than the next number in the array). If such a place occurs more than once, the array cannot be a rotated version of a sorted array.", "estimated_date": 1612656000000}